                      <li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Shows basic understanding of GitHub but fails to address collaboration enhancement effectively</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p>GitHub provides pull requests that allow developers to propose changes and conduct code reviews (cause), which leads to higher code quality and knowledge sharing between team members (effect). The issue tracking system enables teams to organize and prioritize work (cause), resulting in better project management and clear assignment of tasks (effect). Additionally, GitHub's web interface provides visual diff tools and discussion threads (cause), making it easier for distributed teams to communicate about code changes and maintain project documentation (effect).</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
