            <!-- Question 3 -->
            <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
              <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800">Question 3 (5 marks)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 font-medium">
                  A software development team of 5 developers is working on a web application. Compare the advantages and disadvantages of using Git with GitHub versus traditional file sharing methods (such as email attachments or shared network drives) for managing their code.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mb-4">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-4">
                  <div class="space-y-3">
                    <div>
                      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 mb-1">Git/GitHub Advantages:</p>
                      <div class="space-y-2">
                        <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                        <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                        <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 mb-1">Git/GitHub Disadvantages:</p>
                      <div class="space-y-2">
                        <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                        <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 mb-1">Traditional File Sharing Disadvantages:</p>
                      <div class="space-y-2">
                        <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                        <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <details class="mt-6">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-green-50 p-3 rounded text-green-800 font-medium hover:bg-green-100">
                  ðŸ“‹ View Marking Criteria & Sample Answer
                </summary>
                <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
                  <div class="mb-4">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Marking Criteria:</h4>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                      <li><strong>5 marks:</strong> Comprehensive comparison covering Git/GitHub advantages (conflict resolution, history, branching) AND disadvantages (learning curve, complexity) AND traditional method limitations</li>
                      <li><strong>4 marks:</strong> Good comparison covering most aspects but may miss some advantages/disadvantages or lack detail in one area</li>
                      <li><strong>3 marks:</strong> Basic comparison showing understanding of key differences between approaches</li>
                      <li><strong>2 marks:</strong> Shows understanding of version control benefits but comparison lacks depth or structure</li>
                      <li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Shows basic understanding of file management differences but limited comparative analysis</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p><strong>Git/GitHub Advantages:</strong></p>
                      <p>â€¢ Automatic merge conflict resolution prevents loss of work when multiple developers edit the same files</p>
                      <p>â€¢ Complete change history allows reverting to previous versions and understanding why changes were made</p>
                      <p>â€¢ Branch management enables parallel feature development without disrupting the main codebase</p>
                      
                      <p class="mt-3"><strong>Git/GitHub Disadvantages:</strong></p>
                      <p>â€¢ Learning curve requires time investment for team members unfamiliar with Git commands</p>
                      <p>â€¢ Initial setup complexity for repositories, branching strategies, and access permissions</p>
                      
                      <p class="mt-3"><strong>Traditional File Sharing Disadvantages:</strong></p>
                      <p>â€¢ No conflict resolution leads to overwritten files and lost work when multiple developers edit simultaneously</p>
                      <p>â€¢ Lack of change tracking makes it impossible to identify who made specific changes or revert problematic updates</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </details>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 4 -->
            <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
              <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800">Question 4 (3 marks)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 font-medium">
